{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Record an ADR for snapshot strip-key guard form and enforcement boundary — it reads like a one-way door.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f1fb125e200fc7778"],"move_id":"8","move_name":"ADR / one-way-door","subject":"snapshot strip-key guard form and enforcement boundary"},{"coaching":"Run a quick pre-mortem on rollback safety when CREATE events are already compacted: how could this plan fail?","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f8859563982825546"],"move_id":"3","move_name":"pre-mortem","subject":"rollback safety when CREATE events are already compacted"},{"coaching":"Propagate the revision for documentation coverage gaps across child story scope to the child tickets.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f3d561c9cfbfc0aab","f3b085166e7449ec2"],"move_id":"11","move_name":"propagate to children","subject":"documentation coverage gaps across child story scope"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":5,"blocking":0,"dropped":11,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":11,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","ran":true,"references":0,"resolved":0,"status":"pass"},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":11,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":9464,"file_impact":8,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":3,"edges":3,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":11,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"pass","verify_commands_linted":4,"verify_lint_abstained":4},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":2382,"ran":true,"status":"pass","worst_parent_child_pair_tokens":3849},"P9":{"applicable":false,"blocking":false,"file_impact":8,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"floored_criteria":["G3","T8"],"floored_finding_ids":["f8be61ec02b1c3571","f3d561c9cfbfc0aab"],"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":286.8,"llm_calls":22,"llm_ms":741501.8,"total_ms":741883.5,"verify_requests":43},"narrowed":true,"remediation":{"baseline":"signature","eligible":true,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":true,"plan_changed":true,"prior_sidecar":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"signed":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["G3","G4","G6","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","F1","F4","G5","T2","T4","T5e","T7"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Align the pytest -k filter in parent AC2 and e622 AC1: either change parent to `-k 'inbound and recorded'` or change e622 to name test functions so they match `-k inbound_recorded`.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent AC2 prove: 'uv run pytest -q tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_creation_channel.py -k inbound_recorded'","e622 AC1 prove: 'uv run pytest -q tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_creation_channel.py -k \"inbound and recorded\"'","pytest -k 'inbound_recorded' matches nodes whose id substring contains 'inbound_recorded'","pytest -k 'inbound and recorded' matches nodes containing 'inbound' AND 'recorded' independently — different semantics","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Parent AC2's proof command uses `-k inbound_recorded` (a single camelCase/underscore token that pytest matches as a substring), but child e622 AC1 uses `-k \"inbound and recorded\"` (a pytest boolean AND expression selecting tests containing BOTH 'inbound' AND 'recorded'). These two filter expressions select different test node sets: `-k inbound_recorded` matches tests whose node IDs contain the literal string 'inbound_recorded', while `-k \"inbound and recorded\"` matches tests containing 'inbound' AND separately 'recorded' anywhere. A test named 'test_inbound_new_issue_recorded' would be caught by the AND filter but not by the underscore literal. The parent completion verifier will run the parent AC command, which may miss tests the child designed to satisfy its criterion.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f64128aa08f679d5b","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74, parent AC2","norm_id":"nf03d63cb34f388ba","priority":0.5312,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If test functions are named test_inbound_jira_recorded or similar, they satisfy e622 AC1 (-k 'inbound and recorded') but do NOT satisfy the parent AC2 (-k inbound_recorded), causing parent completion verification to show zero collected tests or a test selection mismatch","A developer implementing to e622 spec names tests with 'inbound' and 'recorded' as separate words; the parent verifier finds no tests and wrongly reports AC2 uncovered"],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Update parent AC2 prove command to use '-k \"inbound and recorded\"' to match e622 AC1, OR update e622 AC1 and its test function names to use the underscore-concatenated form 'inbound_recorded' to match the parent.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"broken_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the exact literal string value(s) that constitute 'reconciler' for both the author and env_id inference signals (e.g., by quoting the constant from `inbound_translate._event_meta` or `_jira_key_to_local_id`) so the inference predicate is unambiguous and has a single documented source of truth.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'the genesis/restored author and env_id are both reconciler' — 'reconciler' is never defined as a literal string","Child ticket e622 (Approach Rationale): '_event_meta defaults both author and env_id to reconciler' — names the source but still does not quote the string","src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/apply_inbound_records.py exists but does not define the literal author/env_id string values used by _event_meta","Cached plan-review finding 478dbad49fd29c467501.json flags the same absence: 'the plan never specifies the literal string value(s) that constitute a reconciler identity'"],"finding":"The historical Jira inference predicate — the plan's sole novel behavioral rule — relies on exact string comparison of 'author equals reconciler' and 'env_id equals reconciler', but the plan never specifies what literal string value(s) constitute 'reconciler' for each field, nor does it reference the single source-of-truth location (inbound_translate._event_meta or equivalent). This makes the novel inference rule formally underspecified: an implementer who independently discovers the wrong constant will produce a predicate that silently never fires (or misfires on a rename), with no compile-time or schema-time guard.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f09b45f96d82a59ed","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'Historical records without the field project jira only when all creation-stable signals agree: the ticket ID uses the reconciler-generated jira- prefix and the genesis/restored author and env_id are both reconciler.'","norm_id":"ne73318cd8dd625e9","priority":0.5025,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer guesses 'reconciler' as the author literal, but the actual value is a UUID or a different slug — all legacy Jira tickets fall through to unknown with no test failure until the positive-case test is written against the wrong constant.","A future rename of the reconciler identity string breaks the inference silently after historical records have already been materialized."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"In the Architecture Decisions section (and mirrored in child ticket e622's Approach Rationale), replace 'author and env_id are both reconciler' with the actual quoted constant(s) and add a reference like: 'The exact string is the value produced by inbound_translate._event_meta's author/env_id defaults — reference that constant directly rather than re-encoding it in the reducer helper.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the form of the `_snapshot_strip_keys()` regression guard in story 568c — e.g., add a `_SNAPSHOT_NEVER_STRIP` frozenset containing `creation_channel` and `creation_channel_inferred` and assert at function entry that `_SNAPSHOT_NEVER_STRIP.isdisjoint(_strip)`, making it a runtime guard rather than test-only.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["compact.py:_snapshot_strip_keys() currently returns plain set {'updated_at', 'signature'} with no guard","568c AC says 'Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k placement' — test-only proof, no runtime guard specified","Plan Architecture Decisions: 'Compaction preserves creation_channel and creation_channel_inferred inside SNAPSHOT.data.compiled_state' — behavioral spec only","No mention of whether _snapshot_strip_keys should become an allowlist (strip only known-safe keys) vs. remain a blocklist with an added assertion"],"finding":"Story 568c specifies adding 'a regression guard so the provenance fields cannot enter the strip set' for `_snapshot_strip_keys()`, but does not specify the form of that guard — whether it is a runtime assertion inside the function, an allowlist instead of a blocklist, a separate test-only assertion, or a CI-enforced constant. The existing function is a plain `return {\"updated_at\", \"signature\"}` with no guard mechanism. Without specifying the guard form, an implementer may add only a test (which doesn't protect production) or a comment (which provides no protection at all).","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f1fb125e200fc7778","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"Child ticket 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87 AC: 'creation_channel and creation_channel_inferred never appear on the SNAPSHOT envelope and are not removed by _snapshot_strip_keys'","norm_id":"n6133421119e757de","priority":0.4188,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A future contributor adds 'creation_channel' to _snapshot_strip_keys() during unrelated cleanup (e.g. 'removing provenance fields from snapshots'); the placement test catches it in CI but only if that test is still run.","The guard is implemented only as a pytest assertion that is skipped in fast-test mode, leaving production unprotected."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"In `_snapshot_strip_keys()`, define `_SNAPSHOT_NEVER_STRIP = frozenset({\"creation_channel\", \"creation_channel_inferred\"})` at module level and add `assert _SNAPSHOT_NEVER_STRIP.isdisjoint(strip_set)` before returning, so any future addition of these fields to the strip set raises immediately in production as well as tests.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the exact schema STATE of SNAPSHOT.data.compiled_state after a rollback-then-recompact sequence and either (a) add a guard that the pre-feature compactor MUST NOT re-compact tickets whose existing SNAPSHOT already carries creation_channel, or (b) document this as a DATA LOSS RISK and require that the compactor be pinned to the new binary for any already-compacted tickets before rollback is attempted.","cohort":["T11"],"criteria":["T11"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan states: 'Re-enabling the new reader restores values from CREATE or SNAPSHOT data, so no provenance bytes are lost.'","Plan states: 'Full downgrade to a pre-feature binary remains event-log-safe but hides the public field.'","Plan states compaction 'preserves creation_channel and creation_channel_inferred inside SNAPSHOT.data.compiled_state' — but only under the new compactor, not a rolled-back one.","ABSENCE: no assertion on compiled_state schema state after a rollback-then-recompact sequence; no guard against running the pre-feature compactor on already-compacted (SNAPSHOT-only) tickets post-rollback."],"finding":"The plan's rollback safety claim ('Re-enabling the new reader restores values from CREATE or SNAPSHOT data, so no provenance bytes are lost') is false for tickets where the CREATE event has already been retired by a prior compaction cycle AND a post-rollback pre-feature binary subsequently re-compacts that ticket. In that scenario the SNAPSHOT.data.compiled_state written by the pre-feature compactor will omit creation_channel and creation_channel_inferred, permanently destroying the only surviving copy of those bytes. The plan does not specify a guard against running the pre-feature compactor after rollback, nor does it assert the schema state of compiled_state after a rollback-then-recompact sequence.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8859563982825546","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — rollback paragraph; Risks and Mitigations — Compatibility bullet; AC — 'Legacy-SNAPSHOT fallback … snapshot rebuild'","norm_id":"n1cce1ea2c74b9c9a","priority":0.2567,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A ticket is created with the new writer (creation_channel recorded in CREATE event). Compaction runs, retires the CREATE event, and writes a SNAPSHOT with creation_channel in compiled_state. Rollback is executed, reverting the binary. The pre-feature compactor runs again (e.g., on re-compaction or snapshot rebuild). It writes a new SNAPSHOT without creation_channel. Re-enabling the new reader finds no CREATE event and a SNAPSHOT without the field — provenance bytes are permanently lost. DATA LOSS RISK."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a rollback sub-step: 'Before reverting the binary, identify all tickets that have been compacted under the new writer (SNAPSHOT.data.compiled_state contains creation_channel). Either (a) export/snapshot those values externally before reverting, or (b) document that post-rollback compaction must not run on those tickets. Assert explicitly: after rollback, SNAPSHOT.data.compiled_state for previously-compacted tickets retains creation_channel bytes only if the pre-feature compactor is not re-run; if it is re-run, the field is irrecoverably lost.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7778,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add docs/output-schemas.md to 568c's file_impact and include an AC or What bullet confirming that the output contract documents SNAPSHOT-only replay producing the same creation_channel values as full-log replay.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["568c file_impact: docs/event-schema.md, docs/concurrency.md — docs/output-schemas.md absent","Parent AC11: 'docs/event-schema.md plus docs/output-schemas.md define CREATE/SNAPSHOT placement, the enum, Jira inference, import semantics, plus the distinction from actor/environment/source_* provenance'","Parent AC11 specifies 'SNAPSHOT placement' must be in output-schemas.md — 568c owns SNAPSHOT placement but does not update output-schemas.md","6fe2 and e622 update output-schemas.md for local and Jira/import channels; neither is scoped to document compaction/SNAPSHOT output behavior","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Child 568c's file_impact and ACs do not include docs/output-schemas.md, yet the parent's AC11 requires this file to define 'CREATE/SNAPSHOT placement, the enum, Jira inference, import semantics, plus the distinction from actor/environment/source_* provenance.' The SNAPSHOT placement and compaction semantics that 568c adds to event-schema.md and concurrency.md may need a corresponding entry in output-schemas.md (e.g., clarifying that SNAPSHOT-only replay produces the same creation_channel in consumer outputs). If this is omitted, output-schemas.md will be incomplete after 568c lands.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3b085166e7449ec2","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87","norm_id":"n50db38cdc1925cab","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["After 568c lands, docs/output-schemas.md contains the enum and Jira/import semantics (from 6fe2/e622) but lacks any statement about SNAPSHOT-only replay producing identical consumer-facing creation_channel output — leaving a gap in the output contract documentation that test_schema_coverage.py or make lint could catch"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In 568c's What section, add: 'Update docs/output-schemas.md to state that SNAPSHOT-only replay and snapshot rebuild produce the same creation_channel and creation_channel_inferred values in consumer-facing show/list/export output as full-log replay.' Add docs/output-schemas.md to 568c file_impact.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a described work item for outbound Jira binding/synchronization to the Architecture Decisions and Scope IN sections, clarifying that creation_channel is immutable on the CREATE event and that no outbound reconciler path may inject a competing channel value, then assign the outbound test coverage to the appropriate child story (e.g. e622).","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC3: 'Outbound Jira binding or synchronization preserves the existing local creation channel. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_creation_channel.py -k outbound.'","Scope IN lists: 'CREATE writer plumbing for CLI, MCP, Python, Jira inbound, and NDJSON import' — outbound binding preservation is absent.","Architecture Decisions section describes inbound, import, compaction, and compatibility behaviors but contains no mention of outbound Jira synchronization as a concern for creation_channel.","ABSENCE: no Decomposition task in any of the three child stories is assigned to outbound Jira binding behavior."],"finding":"AC3 ('Outbound Jira binding or synchronization preserves the existing local creation channel') has no corresponding described work in the Architecture, Scope IN, or Decomposition sections. The plan never describes what the outbound Jira path does or must not do to creation_channel, leaving the implementer without a design basis for the required test.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f30844877614c8df5","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC3; Architecture Decisions; Scope IN; Decomposition and Sequencing","norm_id":"n781f2ddfe5b64865","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An implementer reads Scope IN, concludes outbound binding is not in scope, writes no production code for it, then hits a failing AC3 test with no plan guidance on what invariant to enforce.","A reviewer approves Story 2 without outbound coverage because it is not in the story's described deliverables, causing AC3 to remain unverified at merge time."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In Architecture Decisions, add a bullet such as: 'Outbound Jira binding and synchronization operations (e.g. BIND_EXTERNAL, sync events) must not emit a new CREATE event and therefore cannot alter creation_channel. The outbound path is verified to be a no-op with respect to creation provenance.' Then add 'Outbound Jira binding verification' to Scope IN and assign it to story e622.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Reconcile Scope IN and AC3 by either explicitly adding 'Outbound Jira binding preservation verification' to Scope IN (with assignment to story e622) or, if the behavior is architecturally guaranteed by event immutability, demoting AC3 to an informational note rather than a standalone provable criterion.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["COH"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Scope IN: 'CREATE writer plumbing for CLI, MCP, Python, Jira inbound, and NDJSON import.' — no mention of outbound.","AC3: 'Outbound Jira binding or synchronization preserves the existing local creation channel.' — explicitly requires outbound coverage with a named test.","The Decomposition section assigns Jira work to story e622 under 'Jira/import attribution and conservative legacy Jira inference' with no outbound clause."],"finding":"The Scope IN section omits outbound Jira binding/synchronization from the list of in-scope concerns, yet AC3 requires proving preservation behavior on the outbound path. This creates a direct contradiction between what the Scope declares in-scope and what the Acceptance Criteria demand.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f0d6a93c9934b3d02","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope IN vs. Acceptance Criteria — AC3","norm_id":"nd71a38e61e990af7","priority":0.0754,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An implementer scopes story e622 from the Scope IN list and excludes the outbound path, then fails AC3 at acceptance time with no plan-sanctioned design to fall back on."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Replace 'disables or reverts new writers' with an explicit back-out sequence: state that, since no config switch exists, back-out requires a code revert + re-deployment of all writer surfaces, and confirm that the reader projection (returning unknown) survives unchanged so no stored data is lost.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'The operational back-out disables or reverts new writers while retaining the reader projection plus public schema, returning unknown where no recorded value exists.'","'No configuration switch or free-form channel extension is added.'","T4 criterion: 'The remedy is an explicit rollback/back-out plan or expand-contract — acknowledgement alone is insufficient.'"],"finding":"The back-out plan says 'disables or reverts new writers' yet the plan explicitly excludes any configuration switch, making 'disables' meaningless in isolation. The concrete back-out sequence — which must therefore be a code revert + re-deployment — is never stated as such, leaving the rollback path under-specified at the mechanism level.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f380d3613343ae86b","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'The operational back-out disables or reverts new writers while retaining the reader projection plus public schema'","norm_id":"nccf68a80036919c0","priority":0.099,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An on-call engineer needs to roll back the feature after a bad deployment and cannot tell whether 'disables' implies a feature flag (which doesn't exist) or a code revert.","After compaction retires original CREATE events, a reader-only partial downgrade that keeps the schema but stops writing the field still needs a documented sequence of steps to avoid inconsistent state across running instances."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"In Architecture Decisions, replace the back-out sentence with: 'Because no configuration switch is added, the operational back-out is a code revert of writer changes followed by re-deployment; the reader projection and public schema are retained unchanged so that existing stored data (including SNAPSHOT compiled_state) is never lost and channel values are restored automatically when the feature is re-enabled.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify that the Jira inference predicate is implemented in exactly one shared helper/module (referenced by both the reducer processor and snapshot rebuild paths), mirroring the 'define the enum once' contract already stated for the vocabulary.","cohort":["T2","T5e"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan states 'define the enum once, validate at writer boundaries' for the vocabulary but gives no equivalent single-source-of-truth directive for the inference predicate.","Inference predicate must be applied in at least two code paths: reducer projection and SNAPSHOT-only replay/rebuild (per Scope and Decomposition sections).","Absence of a named module or function that owns the predicate logic."],"finding":"The historical Jira inference predicate (three-signal: jira- prefix + reconciler author + reconciler env_id) is a business rule embedded in reducer logic, but the plan does not specify that it lives in a single canonical location analogous to the 'define the enum once' guidance for the vocabulary. If the predicate is encoded in multiple places (e.g., reducer processor AND snapshot rebuild AND documentation independently), it will drift as the reconciler evolves.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f04434bf579b6d33b","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'New writes always record a concrete non-unknown value. Historical records without the field project jira only when all creation-stable signals agree…'","norm_id":"n2e2be2ff9646f568","priority":0.099,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["A future maintainer updates the reconciler's author or env_id convention and must hunt for all predicate sites.","Snapshot rebuild and live projection diverge silently if the predicate is copy-pasted rather than shared."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a sentence to Architecture Decisions: 'The three-signal Jira inference predicate is extracted into a single shared helper (e.g., rebar/_engine/creation_channel.py) imported by both the reducer processor and the snapshot rebuild path; it must not be duplicated.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an ADR or CLAUDE.md section capturing the creation-channel provenance design decision, including: closed-vocabulary rationale, inference-marker trust boundary, import vs. source_* distinction, and the additive/no-migration compatibility contract.","cohort":["T2","T5e"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan lists docs/event-schema.md and docs/output-schemas.md as the only documentation targets.","No mention of CLAUDE.md, ADR, or design-doc update for the architectural decision.","Architecture Decisions section contains nuanced, non-obvious rationale (inference marker trust boundary, additive contract, compaction envelope semantics) that belongs in a durable decision record."],"finding":"The plan introduces a novel cross-cutting architectural decision (immutable creation-channel provenance, historical inference semantics, import vs. source_* distinction, compaction/snapshot durability contract) that spans six components, yet mentions only updates to docs/event-schema.md and docs/output-schemas.md. No ADR or CLAUDE.md entry is planned to capture the rationale, trade-offs, and trust-boundary semantics for future maintainers.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3259ab8ef05b7cae","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope (IN) — 'Reducer projection, public ticket-state/output schemas, typed surfaces, export behavior, and documentation'; AC — 'docs/event-schema.md plus docs/output-schemas.md define…'","norm_id":"n097881f033b8d3ab","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A new contributor encounters the creation_channel_inferred: true field and cannot find the reasoning for why it is 'diagnostic metadata, not a security attestation'.","A future team member adding a new ingress (e.g., GitHub reconciler) lacks a canonical record of the vocabulary extension process."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Document in the inference spec (Architecture Decisions, story e622 Approach Rationale, and docs/event-schema.md) that the three-signal predicate matches only the default `reconciler` author/env string literals and will produce `unknown` for historical events written by reconciler instances that ran with non-default REBAR_AUTHOR or REBAR_ENV_ID; if non-default deployments must be supported, extend the predicate or provide an operator-configurable inference allowlist.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["_event_meta() returns: author = _rebar_env('AUTHOR', 'reconciler'), env_id = _rebar_env('ENV_ID', 'reconciler') — these become the literal values recorded in historical CREATE envelopes, not the literal string 'reconciler' when env vars are set","Plan inference rule: 'the genesis/restored author and env_id are both reconciler' — hard-codes the string literal 'reconciler'","Story e622 Approach Rationale: 'inbound_translate._event_meta defaults both author and env_id to reconciler' — the word 'defaults' reveals the gap for non-default deployments","Plan's own scoping: 'never infer CLI, MCP, Python, or import' — conservative by design but no documentation of the operator-customization edge"],"finding":"The three-signal legacy Jira inference predicate (jira-* id AND author==\"reconciler\" AND env_id==\"reconciler\") silently produces `unknown` for historical tickets from any reconciler deployment where REBAR_AUTHOR or REBAR_ENV_ID were set to non-default values, because _event_meta() uses _rebar_env() with a fallback of 'reconciler' — meaning those deployed values were recorded in historical CREATE events and will never match the literal string. The plan treats this as a zero-false-positive design choice but does not document or scope this degradation for operator-customized deployments.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f95f5981699f1189b","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions (inference predicate) / story e622 Approach Rationale / src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_translate.py:_event_meta()","norm_id":"na76d925dbb419e94","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["A deployment that set REBAR_AUTHOR=jira-bridge or REBAR_ENV_ID=prod-jira-sync will have historical Jira-created tickets with non-'reconciler' author/env in their CREATE events; the inference predicate will produce 'unknown' for all of them rather than 'jira', silently contradicting the auditor's expectation.","A migration between reconciler instances with different env configs produces inconsistent historical inference across tickets created in different eras."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Name the canonical Python symbol for the creation_channel vocabulary (e.g. `CREATION_CHANNELS: frozenset[str]`) in the Architecture Decisions section or child 6fe2's spec, parallel to how `KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES`/`TAG_DELTA` are defined in `_version.py`, so child e622 and 568c can import the same constant.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Grep of entire src/rebar tree for 'creation_channel' returns zero matches — enum does not yet exist","Plan text: 'closed compact vocabulary cli, mcp, python, jira, import, unknown' but names no Python symbol","Child 6fe2: 'Add a contract test that prevents runtime/schema vocabulary drift' — implies a symbol to import, but the symbol name is unspecified","Parallel prior art: KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES, TAG_DELTA, KEY_ADD, KEY_REVOKE are all named module-level constants in _version.py that child stories import directly"],"finding":"The six-value creation_channel enum vocabulary is referenced throughout the plan and all three child tickets but has no authoritative definition location at the epic level — the plan defers its definition to child 6fe2 (common.schema.json + _version.py runtime constant), but neither the plan nor the child specifies the runtime constant's name, type (frozenset? tuple? TypeAlias?), or the module-level symbol an implementer or drift-prevention test should import. An executor of child e622 or 568c cannot reference a canonical symbol without inspecting 6fe2's delivered artifact.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa63dfa5652e4c8e9","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions / Decomposition — 'Add the canonical creation-channel enum'; child 6fe2 'Add the matching runtime constant to src/rebar/reducer/_version.py'","norm_id":"n87cca3cdcba5582e","priority":0.066,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An implementer of child e622 writes 'CREATION_CHANNELS = frozenset({...})' while a reviewer expects 'VALID_CREATION_CHANNELS'; the drift-prevention contract test breaks or targets the wrong symbol.","Child 568c's regression guard cannot reference the canonical set without knowing the symbol name, leading to a duplicated inline set."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"In child 6fe2's 'Files' section for `src/rebar/reducer/_version.py`, add: 'Define `CREATION_CHANNELS = frozenset({\"cli\", \"mcp\", \"python\", \"jira\", \"import\", \"unknown\"})` and `_LIVE_CREATION_CHANNELS = CREATION_CHANNELS - {\"unknown\"}` as named module-level constants, mirroring the KNOWN_EVENT_TYPES pattern; the contract test and all writers import from this symbol.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] In story 568c, explicitly state that the `creation_channel` migration hook in `process_snapshot` reads `state['ticket_id']`, `state.get('author')`, and `state.get('env_id')` (restored by the verbatim loop) and specify its position in the existing migration sequence (after the keyring hook, to avoid ordering interactions with managed_refs/parent_id).","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["_processors.py:process_snapshot (line 744-793): verbatim restore loop followed by three ordered migration hooks; no `author` or `env_id` guard","Story 568c: 'A legacy snapshot with jira-* ticket_id plus reconciler author/env_id becomes inferred jira' — requires author/env_id in state at hook time","process_create stores state['author'] from event.get('author') and state['env_id'] from event.get('env_id'); these ARE carried in compiled_state and restored by the verbatim loop — but this is not stated in the plan","SNAPSHOT-only replay (no CREATE in log): compiled_state carries author/env_id from the original CREATE's compiled_state, so the fields ARE available — but again, not stated"],"finding":"The plan specifies that `process_snapshot` must run the legacy projection helper 'only when creation_channel is absent' after restoring compiled_state, but does not specify where in the existing migration hook sequence this new block sits. The current `process_snapshot` body contains three ordered migration hooks (managed_refs, attestations, keyring), each with distinct `if key not in compiled_state` guards and ordering rationale. The creation_channel hook has an additional subtlety: it must fire on restored state (after the verbatim restore loop), yet it depends on `ticket_id`, `author`, and `env_id` being available in `state` — fields that are restored by the verbatim loop. The plan does not confirm these fields are available in state at the time the hook fires, nor specify whether a SNAPSHOT-only replay (no preceding CREATE) has `author`/`env_id` available from compiled_state.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fd0bbcd058cae6dc5","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Story 568c 'What' section — 'After process_snapshot restores compiled_state, run the same legacy projection helper used after CREATE only when creation_channel is absent'","norm_id":"na84426e65178e244","priority":0.066,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An implementer writing the hook assumes `state.get('author')` is always set after snapshot restore, but a corrupt/partial compiled_state omits it — inference fires against None and produces wrong results.","The hook is placed BEFORE the managed_refs migration (which is order-sensitive) causing a subtle interaction with the parent_id field used for managed_refs seeding."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] In e622, explicitly document and test the inference helper's input contract (the exact dict keys it reads) and add at least one AC or test confirming it is callable with compiled_state-shaped input, not only raw CREATE event data.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["e622 Scope OUT: 'SNAPSHOT-only legacy inference, compaction'","568c What: 'After process_snapshot restores compiled_state, run the same legacy projection helper used after CREATE only when creation_channel is absent'","e622 adds the legacy projection helper to reducer/_processors.py with no AC testing it on SNAPSHOT-restored state","568c AC3: 'A pre-feature SNAPSHOT lacking both keys projects inferred Jira only for the exact three-signal predicate' — relies on the e622 helper being callable in this context","No e622 AC verifies the helper's interface contract (what data shape it accepts) beyond the CREATE projection context","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Child e622 explicitly scopes out 'SNAPSHOT-only legacy inference' yet the inference helper it builds in reducer/_processors.py is expected by 568c to function correctly when invoked from the post-SNAPSHOT-restore path in process_snapshot. The e622 spec defines the helper purely in the context of full-log CREATE-based projection and does not specify or test the helper's behavior when called with compiled_state fields populated from a SNAPSHOT restore (where raw event metadata is unavailable). If the helper reads from event-level fields that differ from compiled_state fields at restore time, 568c's AC3 will fail unexpectedly.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc772f9981b62fe53","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 (Scope OUT), child 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87 (What / AC3)","norm_id":"nec7cfa04abe22533","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["e622 implements the helper reading from event-level author/env_id fields that exist on a CREATE event dict but not in compiled_state; 568c calls it with compiled_state and receives KeyError or wrong result","The helper works in CREATE context but compiled_state uses different key names (e.g., 'genesis_author' vs 'author') causing silent misattribution after SNAPSHOT restore"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a unit test to e622 (in test_creation_channel.py or a shared helper test) that calls the legacy projection helper with a compiled_state dict (ticket_id, author, env_id keys) and confirms it produces the correct inferred/unknown output — establishing the interface contract that 568c depends on.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Extract the 'reconciler' author/env_id default strings from `_event_meta()` into named module-level constants (e.g. `_RECONCILER_DEFAULT_AUTHOR`, `_RECONCILER_DEFAULT_ENV_ID`) in `inbound_translate.py` and specify that the inference predicate in `_processors.py` imports and compares against these same constants rather than re-stating the string literals.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["inbound_translate.py:_event_meta() line 166-167: `_rebar_env('ENV_ID', 'reconciler')`, `_rebar_env('AUTHOR', 'reconciler')` — the 'reconciler' default is an env-overridable default, not a constant","Plan text: 'the genesis/restored author and env_id are both reconciler' — names the string value but not a shared constant","Child e622: 'inbound_translate._jira_key_to_local_id generates jira-* IDs and _event_meta defaults both author and env_id to reconciler' — references _event_meta but does not propose extracting the defaults as named constants","No module-level `RECONCILER_AUTHOR` or `RECONCILER_ENV_ID` constant exists anywhere in the codebase (grep confirms)"],"finding":"The three-signal Jira inference predicate depends on exact literal string values ('reconciler') for author and env_id comparisons, but these literals are only implicit in `_event_meta()` in `inbound_translate.py` (which returns `_rebar_env('ENV_ID', 'reconciler')` and `_rebar_env('AUTHOR', 'reconciler')`). The plan describes the predicate behaviorally but never names the constants, leaving a risk that the inference helper hard-codes the string 'reconciler' independently while the actual default could change via environment variable override — producing silent false negatives.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8be61ec02b1c3571","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'genesis/restored author and env_id are both reconciler'; child e622 'All comparisons are exact'","norm_id":"n3a8b452f7c46774e","priority":0.2063,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A deployment sets REBAR_ENV_ID=jira-bridge; legacy records written before the override carry 'reconciler'; the inference predicate hard-codes 'reconciler' and correctly fires, but future records from the overridden env never match — silent false negatives on new Jira-created tickets.","A maintainer renames the default from 'reconciler' to 'rebar-reconciler' in _event_meta; the inference helper's hard-coded literal silently stops matching all historical records."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add `uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py && make lint` to e622 AC7 (or a new AC) and to 568c AC6 or a new AC so documentation coverage is re-verified after each story's doc additions.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Parent AC11 prove: 'uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py && make lint'","6fe2 AC5 prove includes test_schema_coverage.py — runs BEFORE e622 and 568c add their documentation","e622 file_impact includes docs/event-schema.md, docs/cli-reference.md, docs/output-schemas.md; none of its ACs re-run test_schema_coverage.py","568c file_impact includes docs/event-schema.md, docs/concurrency.md; none of its ACs include test_schema_coverage.py or make lint","e622 verify_commands: DD-X1, DD-X2, DD-X3 — none invoke test_schema_coverage.py or make lint","568c verify_commands: DD-S1, DD-S2, DD-S3 — none invoke test_schema_coverage.py or make lint","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Parent AC11 requires `uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py && make lint` as its final proof, but only child 6fe2 runs test_schema_coverage.py (in its AC5). Children e622 and 568c both add new documentation to event-schema.md, output-schemas.md, cli-reference.md, and concurrency.md AFTER 6fe2's AC5 runs, yet neither e622 nor 568c re-runs test_schema_coverage.py or make lint in any of their ACs. If test_schema_coverage.py validates that all documented concepts match schema definitions, it must pass after all documentation additions are complete — but no child AC proves it at that point.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3d561c9cfbfc0aab","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74, child 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87","norm_id":"nd479c067e23fc128","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["e622 adds Jira/import semantics to event-schema.md but test_schema_coverage.py is never re-run to confirm those additions satisfy the coverage test — a documentation gap could exist undetected until parent AC11 is attempted","568c adds SNAPSHOT placement semantics to event-schema.md and compaction semantics to concurrency.md but test_schema_coverage.py is not re-verified — the parent completion check may fail","make lint is required at parent close but no child after 6fe2 runs it"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Append a final AC to both e622 and 568c: 'docs/event-schema.md, docs/output-schemas.md, and related documentation pass test_schema_coverage.py and make lint after this story's additions. Prove with: uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py && make lint.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"8040396f855aed6a","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":286.8,"llm_calls":22,"llm_ms":741501.8,"total_ms":741883.5,"verify_requests":43},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591